name: Armstrong Student Center
description: Located in the center of campus,  get anything you want from burgers and shakes to stir-fry to pizza to custom smoothies!

name: Haines
description: Soups, salads and sandwiches, breakfast sandwiches and coffee.

name: Pulley Diner
description: Step back in time to this 1950s-style diner, open 24/7. The menu includes favorites like burgers, chicken tenders and milkshakes.

name: Sundial Pizza
description: Grab a pizza slice, a whole pie prepared in our stone oven or an express pasta. You can now order custom calzones, pizzas and pasta through GET.

name: Sundial UPE
description: Fresh sandwiches, salads, and snacks made and packaged at Miami's Demske culinary Support Center.

name: Mein Street & StrEATS
description: Featuring an oversized Teppanyaki grill, select a protein, vegetable blend and sauce to create your own stir fry. Wing Bar where you can get wings hand-tossed in the sauce of your choice, along with chicken sandwiches, mozzarella sticks and more!

name: Toasted Bagel
description: Your favorite home-style meats and sides with the occasional menu twist to keep you coming back for more.

name: Cafe Lux
description: Envision the perfect cup of coffee in an European-inspired venue. Accompany your drink with a rotating selection of pastries, soups, and sandwiches.

name: Bell Tower Commons
description: A combination of buffet and market. Buffet features salads, soup, pasta, pizza, burgers, chicken, stir fry, tacos, burritos, and bakery items. Grab a custom sandwich or coffee from the market!

name: Dividend$
description: Located in the Farmer School of Business, Dividends, a popular lunchtime location, offers five unique menu options.

name: Garden Commons
description: Take a trip through the seasons while you experience the beauty of Miami’s campus with an extensive menu to match! This buffet location features four stations including Asian, Italian, and comfort favorites.

name: King Cafe
description: Take a break from studying to grab a quick meal or recharge with caffeine at King Café. Conveniently located inside of King Library, this location offers students a quick and easy way to purchase food, coffee beverages, or smoothies.

name: Market Street at MacCracken
description: The largest of our campus convenience markets, Market Street at MacCracken has everything you need to stock your fridge or pantry, entertain friends, or grab a meal on the go. Common toiletries, health & beauty items, and medications are also available.

name: Martin Dining Commons
description: Dine-in at the buffet with popular concepts like Ciao Italian favorites, Harvest Greens salad and fruit bar, and  healthy-conscious Winning Seasonings.

name: Maplestreet Commons
description: One of our biggest buffets offering everything from made-to-order stir fry to a salsa and hummus bar. Don't forget about favorites such as pizza, pasta, grill items, and our Southwest station.

name: Western Dining Commons
description: Recognized as one of the top 36 Dining Halls in the country, Western Dining Commons brings you everything you could want—a buffet, market, and a tea house.

name: Regional Campus Dining
description: Miami Dining is proud to serve the regional campuses in Hamilton and Middletown. Both campus feature a coffee concept and a made-to-order meal concepts.

name: Mporium
description: Stop at this campus market for a quick snack and coffee or stock your pantry.
